sights.quote: Birthplace of Wolfgang Mozart in 1756, now a house museum with tours detailing his young life.

sights.name: Mozartplatz
sights.quote: This large courtyard is best known for its memorial statue of composer Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart.

sights.name: Haus der Natur
sights.quote: Massive, interactive science & natural history museum, also offering an aquarium & reptile zoo.

sights.name: Fortress Hohensalzburg
sights.quote: Huge 11th-century fortress complex on a hilltop with views over city to the Alps & museums.

sights.name: Schloss Hellbrunn
sights.quote: 17th-century Renaissance palace & pleasure gardens with grottos, novelty fountains & a theater.

sights.name: Salzburg Zoo Hellbrunn
sights.quote: Family-friendly zoo with on-site dining & animals from Africa, Eurasia, Australia & the Americas.

sights.name: The Eagle's Nest
sights.quote: Hitler's former mountain-top base reached by elevator, now the site of a restaurant with views.

sights.name: Mirabellgarten
sights.quote: Elegant landscaping, pathways & floral displays on lush grounds fronting the Mirabell Palace.

sights.name: Mirabell Palace
sights.quote: Iconic, 17th-century palace with ornamental gardens, plus classical concerts in the lavish ballroom.

sights.name: Holy Trinity Church
sights.quote: Prominent Catholic church completed in 1702, with a sizable dome fresco & baroque architecture.

sights.name: Haus der Natur
sights.quote: Massive, interactive science & natural history museum, also offering an aquarium & reptile zoo.

sights.name: Franciscan Church
sights.quote: Franciscan church with architectural details (including a Baroque interior) from several periods.

sights.name: DomQuartier Salzburg
sights.quote: A UNESCO World Heritage Site, this expansive Baroque complex offers art & cultural history tours.

sights.name: Salzburg Museum
sights.quote: Spacious art museum featuring contemporary & 19th-century works by Salzburg artists.

sights.name: Wasser.Spiegel - Wassermuseum am Mönchsberg
sights.quote: Compact museum featuring exhibitions on the history of Salzburg's water supply, with water tastings.

sights.name: Schloss Hellbrunn
sights.quote: 17th-century Renaissance palace & pleasure gardens with grottos, novelty fountains & a theater.

sights.name: Salzburger Weihnachtsmuseum
sights.quote: Quaint museum & cafe featuring an extensive private collection of Christmas figurines.
